node.text: Yes please! @tinatchen joins me today to discuss the #CTC and give you all of the details you’ll need to sign up — did you know that visiting www.ChildTaxCredit.gov and filling out your info ALSO qualifies you to receive any stimulus checks you might have missed due to your filing status!? — or to help your loved ones do so. This money is a game changer for ALL families. In every state. Because the quality of children’s lives isn’t partisan. Let’s go, friends!

node.text: American families are getting the support they need, starting this week. This will reduce child poverty by over 50%! Nearly all families with kids will qualify. And when families do well, the economy does well. For every $1 we invest in families, we see $8 returned into the economy. So this helps everyone. I’m deeply grateful for Congresswoman DeLauro’s work on getting this policy enacted, and deeply grateful to President Biden for prioritizing families and uplifting so many! Here we go!! Visit www.ChildTaxCredit.gov to figure out what you’ll begin receiving this month!

node.title: Talking about the Child Tax Credit with the legendary @rosa_delauro!

node.text: [CONT’D 2] Jared Yates Sexton rightly pointed out that “The entire reason we have rules to expel members of Congress is to expel members of Congress who have openly endorsed the murder of their colleagues, traffic in racist, virulent conspiracy theories, and have worked to overthrow the government.” That day? Over 140 officers injured. Two officers are dead from the attack; two from suicide. Officers without helmets sustained brain injuries. One officer has two cracked ribs and two smashed spinal discs. One officer is going to lose his eye; one was stabbed with a metal fence stake. And people like Lauren Boebert gave tours?! Greene says these are patriots?? Ted Cruz spoke at the rallies screaming “don’t go quietly!!” Madison Cawthorn told supporters “you can threaten” your reps over the election. Don’t even get me started on Josh Hawley. And these are the same people, who despite having facts about @ayannapressley’s panic buttons having been ripped out of her Congressional office ahead of the attack, despite the published evidence that Christopher Miller, Trump's then-acting defense secretary, on Jan 4 issued a memorandum stating that authorities at the Capitol were not allowed to use weapons, wear helmets or body armor, interact physically with protestors, employ riot control agents, or even make arrests, essentially guaranteeing that the insurrection would succeed, want to move on!? You’re damn right I agree with Rep @jackiespeier that inciting insurrection and being a terrorist sympathizer in the halls of Congress or the Senate means you should be labeled as such. But what Breitbart did, falsely claiming I am “advocating for labeling [ALL] Republicans as terrorists,” misrepresenting my agreement with Congressional leaders about the standard to which their colleagues are held and obfuscating my point to claim I’m apparently passing judgment on anyone who’s ever voted as a registered conservative? It’s egregious and irresponsible. It lacks context or the critical thinking skills required to make nuanced points. But the thing is?? They know that. “News” editors do pay attention, and do know what the argument is. [CONT]

There is so much going on in the world, and sometimes the best way to act to save it is right in your own backyard. My fellow California residents! We must VOTE “NO” on the Recall. Info from @sarah.epperson:

Send back your ballot ASAP - Sept 14th
Registration ends: Aug 30th RegisterToVote.CA.gov
Track your ballot: WheresMyBallot.SOS.CA.gov 
Get more info: SOS.CA.gov/elections
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
VOTE “NO” ON RECALL:
QUESTION 1 (on the ballot)
California Gubernatorial Recall Election
Vote Yes or No
⭕️YES = against Newsom & is to kick him out of office
⚫️ NO = for Newsom & to keep him as governor
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“If over 50% of voters #vote "YES" on the 1st question, @GavinNewsom will be removed & the candidate who receives the most votes on the 2nd question will replace him, even if they do NOT win a majority of votes. 🚨 In other words, a minority of #voters could determine who will be the next #Governor of #California. This is a terrifying thought” @NRDC_org
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
@MatthaneySF: You can dislike #GavinNewsom & still #VoteNoOnTheRecall
The question is WHAT is at stake, not who.
What is at stake:
🥵 Climate Change
😷 Vaccines / C0VlD
💵 Minimum wage
🌎 Environmental protection
🧑‍⚕️ Abortion rights
📚 Public Education
🩺 Healthcare
🔫 Gun Violence prevention
👩‍👩‍👦‍👦 Support for Immigrants
⚖️ Justice reform
🧓 The Senate
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
@UCBerkeleyOffical poll found that 47% of likely California voters supported recalling the Democratic governor, compared with 50% who opposed removing Newsom from office — a difference just shy of the survey’s margin of error.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Even though #Democrat voters far outnumber #Republicans in California, the #GOP ’s enthusiasm over the recall promises to inflate the potency of the anti-Newsom vote in Sept. Nearly 90% of Republicans expressed a high level of interest in the #RecallElection while just 58% of Democrats & 53% of independent voters were as interested.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The findings dispel the notion that California’s solid Dem voter majority will provide an impenetrable shield for Newsom, & reveal a vulnerability created by a recall effort that has energized Republicans & been met with indifference by many Dems & independents.” @LATimes

This.
This place.
The land of my past.
Of my heritage.
Of my mother, and hers, and hers before.
Of Mario and his oxen.
Basil grown in the garden.
Wine made in the basement.

Comes my future.
Him.
Wine is our passion.
We raise bees at home.
We grow basil too.
And now, tomatoes from Luca, Italy. In Los Angeles.

Our families’ pasts, overlap with our present.
We see a future on the horizon.
We choose it.
Them, eventually.
Ours.

This day. Forever.
I’m beaming.
I never knew.
Now I do.
I know.
This.
You.
💫

node.text:
To be in motion …

Ten days of at-home isolation
Five PCR tests (every 48 hours during those days)
Double masks + face shields.
Five days of near isolation on arrival.
Two more tests during that period.
Two vaccine doses that made it at all possible (thank you science and @jessicamalatyrivera and @doctor.darien for everything).

After 18 months of working almost exclusively from home (worth it to leave for #GoodSamCBS and #FalsePositive) thanks to @workinprogress and @dramaqueensoth and the modern technology that makes those shows possible from inside a converted closet at my house…

All for this.

This view.
This homeland.
This air of my mother’s mother, and her mother, and so on.
It smells like home, somehow.

The gratitude I feel for the privilege of being able to take such precautions and such a trip in the first place?
Immeasurable.
For my favorite human who made me feel safe to adventure again?
Boundless.

As a globe, we are learning to move again.
I’m not sure I have my sea legs yet — and by “sea legs” I mean SEE legs … seeing humans on the outside — but I’m working on them!

Rest is sacred.
Retreat is a gift.
I’m just … 💫 … bursting.

Love, 🇮🇹

node.text:
I am constantly and immensely grateful for the community of women in my life. Brilliant, creative, capable, supportive, funny, dynamic women. In watching them and they way they live their lives, in experiencing my own in the world, and in being someone who is honored to communicate with all of you here, and hear your stories and witness your lives? One thing is clear to me. We show up. Do our best. Give it our all. And we are, because of a system that wasn’t designed to benefit us, often made to work harder. Period. As our friends @argent said recently, “Women work, but the status quo doesn’t.”

What do we mean by that? Over 2 million women have left the workforce since the start of the #pandemic. Even before #COVID-19 our economy was not built to support women —especially women of color. The data makes it clear: Women work, work, work but no the status quo doesn’t. Women take on more of the work of caring for children and the family. That data? Women spend seven more years on average performing more household work than men (SEVEN!? YEARS! TY for the info @melindafrenchgates) And according to a recent @nytimes piece, experts are saying that due to the pandemic, it will “take our women 10 years to get back” in the workplace. It’s simply not okay.

So what’s the solution? There will need to be many — and we are looking at you policy makers! — but “many” also means we can get creative and each use our unique abilities to help out. Our friends @argent x @timesupnow x @linkedin are doing just that. They’ve created a platform to connect #jobseekers with #employers — centering the voices of women and those impacted — to build a more equitable and sustainable economy!! One that offers safe, fair, flexible, and dignified opportunities for ALL.

Want to get involved? Join us as we get our communities #BackToWork AT argentwork.com/backtowork. #work #backtowork #letsgoladies #workingwomen 💙🧡❤️

*And be sure to check out what all of the wonderful humans in this slideshow have to say about the dignity of work, and community. I’m always honored to work with these incredible folks ✊

node.text:
My sweet sweet Markie… I don’t have the words. Devastated comes to mind. Crushed. Heartbroken. This woman. This ray of sunshine. Pure light. And goodness.

Markie Post was a TV icon. Bold. Funny. Always in on the joke, usually before the rest of the room. Always holding a deeper perspective on a character’s reality than what was on the page.

When I lived in a box that made it deeply difficult to be a woman who could exist as one … and … breathe? Markie came in with arms to envelop me and eyes that fired both kindness and lightning storms into the room as she held me, and likewise called other women into her safe space. She did it all with a smile and a laugh, and with more wisdom than most of us could ever hope to learn or muster.

I loved her on Night Court. I blushed when she came to Chicago. To play MY onscreen mom!? And I loved her in our hair and makeup trailer and at cozy dinners over endless laughter and as I watched her eyes light up when she spoke of her husband and her daughters. When she called me an “uncommon woman” I melted.

Markie was the kind of set momma who made you feel invincible and gave you permission to be vulnerable and tender. I’ll never forget that mystical power. That rare duality.

We spoke about getting each of our overlapping onscreen families together. @hilarieburton, @tylerhilton, and @meganparkithere. That overlap!? We LOVED how lucky we’d been to share two TV families. And then life, different locations, and a pandemic got in the way. I will forever curse the missed opportunity of that reunion dinner we hadn’t had just yet.

Hug the people you love. Don’t say “we’ll do it soon, honey.” Dont wait until everyone is “back in town and it’s easy.” Do it now. Make the trek. Don’t miss your moments.

To her family? Michael. Kate. Daisy. The ones she lit UP when she spoke of? The ones who put a twinkle and a sparkle in her eye? Man oh man she loved you. Man oh man am I sorry to see her go. How grateful I am that you shared her with me. That I got to borrow her and her boundless heart. Thank you, forever.

#MarkiePost #MyForeverBunny ♥️🐰💔
